<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407076>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Pseudoodes cribristernis Bates, 1892 (A–B: female specimen, China, Yunnan Prov., Fugong County, Guquan Village; C: male specimen, same locality; D–E: female specimen, Thailand, Chiang Dao). A: mentum; B: prosternal process; C: right protarsomeres; D: left gonocoxite, ventral view; E: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–C, E); = 0.2 mm (Fig. D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407076/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407086>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Pseudoodes coelestinus Chaudoir, 1882 (A: male specimen, Malaysia, Mulu National Park; B: male specimen, Malaysia, Kapit; C–D: female specimen, Malaysia, Mulu National Park).A: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B: same, dorsal view; C: left gonocoxite, ventral view; D: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–B, D); = 0.2 mm (Fig. C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407086/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407100>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Sundaoodes hainanensis sp. n. (A–H:holotype; I–J: female paratype).A: habitus and labels; B: head and pronotum; C: mentum; D: prosternal process; E: left metepisternum and metacoxa; F: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; G: same, ventral view; H: same, dorsal view; I: left gonocoxite, ventral view; J: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 2 mm (Fig. A); = 1 mm (Figs B, E); = 0.5 mm (Figs C–D, F–H, J); = 0.2 mm (Fig. I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407100/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407104>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Sundaoodes kalimantanensis sp. n. (A, C–D, G–H: holotype; B, E–F, I–K: paratype). A: habitus and labels; B: habitus; C: head and pronotum; D: mentum (white spots show locations of submental setiferous punctures); E: prosternal process; F: left metepisternum and metacoxa; G: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; H: same, anterior half, dorsal view; I: left gonocoxite, ventral view; J: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, dorsal view; K: same, ventral view. Scale lines = 2 mm (Figs A–B); = 1 mm (Figs C, F); = 0.5 mm (Fig. D–E, G–H, J–K); = 0.2 mm (Fig. I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407104/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

